FootnoteText: Obesity is defined as body mass index (BMI)-for-age and sex =95th percentile based on the 2000 CDC growth chart; BMI was calculated from measured weight and height (weight [kg]/ height [m²]). Children with missing values of height, weight, and BMI were excluded. In addition, children with biological implausible values for height, weight, and BMI defined as the following z-scores values, were excluded from the analyses: height-for-age< -5.0 or >4.0, weight-for-age< -5.0 or >8.0, and BMI-for-age< -4.0 or >8.0.
